<p>Both CDF and the OpsBridge Suite require databases to be created prior to the installation. Since the Postgres RDS instance is only available internally, a Postgres client will need to be installed on one of the nodes. The Bastion server will be used in this example, however any of the Master or Worker nodes can be used as well.
</p>
<ol><li>Connect to the Bastion server and install the Postgres 9.5 client by running these commands. <br> " yum install <a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://download.postgresql.org/pub/repos/yum/9.5/redhat/rhel-7-x86_64/pgdg-centos95-9.5-3.noarch.rpm">https://download.postgresql.org/pub/repos/yum/9.5/redhat/rhel-7-x86_64/pgdg-centos95-9.5-3.noarch.rpm</a>" <br> " yum install postgresql95"</li>
<li>Connect to the Postgres Server by running this command: <br> " /usr/pgsql-9.5/bin/psql -h &lt;fqdn of Postgres RDS Server&gt; --username=postgres"</li>
<li>Create a role for the Suite databases at the "postgres=&gt;" prompt <br> 'CREATE ROLE &lt;user&gt; WITH LOGIN PASSWORD '&lt;password&gt;';</li>
<li>Grant the role to the Postgres user <br> 'GRANT &lt;user&gt; to postgres;'</li>
<li>Create the databases for both CDF and OpsBridge  <br> 'CREATE DATABASE cdf_idm OWNER &lt;user&gt;;' <br>'CREATE DATABASE autopassdb OWNER &lt;user&gt;;' <br>'CREATE DATABASE bvd OWNER &lt;user&gt;;' <br>'CREATE DATABASE rtsm OWNER &lt;user&gt;;' <br>'CREATE DATABASE mgmt OWNER &lt;user&gt;;' <br>'CREATE DATABASE event OWNER &lt;user&gt;;'</li>
<li>Create extensions for each of the Suite databases by running these commands while connected to Postgres with psql: <br>  '\c event' <br> 'CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS "uuid-ossp";' <br> '\c event' 'CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS "uuid-ossp";' <br> Repeat these commands on the rtsm and mgmt databases.</li></ol>
<p><br>
</p>
